reviewText: I will enjoy my christmas this year thank you.

Got this for "A Christmas Story" only. "Jack Frost" is just OK, and "The Year Without a Santa Claus" TV remake is probably one of the worst Christmas films I've ever seen, although Harvey Fierstein's "Heat Miser" is a view of the future seeing what our current president looks like and is surprisingly well staged. Had I really thought about it past the low price, I probably would have bought "A Christmas Story" as a single feature with all the extras so I didn't have to save it with two films I probably won't ever watch again or lend to friends, at least those whom I want to keep as friends.
Three great Xmas movies at a very reasonable price.
Case came broken. Just wanted a replacement. Jack Frost great. Other two ok.
Three great Christmas stories that the whole family can enjoy over and over at a very good price. Amazon has my vote. Thanks for the dvd of "String of Holiday Classics" 3- pack.
